                <div class="row" style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--mut);margin-bottom:8px">Across 50 of your prompts, routing saved <b style="color:var(--green)">$41 (54%)</b> · 96% of outputs judged non-inferior to the standard model.</div>
                <div class="sxs2">
                  <div class="col"><h5>Prompt</h5>"Classify: 'I was charged twice this month' — billing / technical / sales?"</div>
                  <div class="col win"><h5>ModelPilot → Haiku · $0.0004</h5>billing &nbsp;<span class="pill save">✓ non-inferior</span></div>
                </div>
                <div class="sxs2" style="margin-top:8px">
                  <div class="col"><h5>Standard → Opus · $0.0028</h5>billing</div>
                  <div class="col win"><h5>identical answer · saved 86%</h5>same result, 7× cheaper</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="scene" data-scene="4">
                <div class="reqlog">
                  <div class="row"><span class="m">$</span> modelpilot gateway --mode autopilot --port 8400</div>
                  <div class="row"><b>autopilot ON</b> <span class="m">— routing live, quality-gated</span></div>
                  <div class="row">saved this week &nbsp;<span class="ok">$298 realized (40%)</span></div>
                  <div class="row">quality parity &nbsp;<span class="ok">holding</span> <span class="m">— regen/escalation flat vs holdout control</span></div>
                  <div class="row">auto-tuning &nbsp;<span class="ok">on</span> <span class="m">— savings climb as it learns your traffic</span></div>
